article.description: Loyola (Md) rallies past Boston U 91-86 in OT
article.headline: Loyola (Md) rallies past Boston U 91-86 in OT
article.linkText: Loyola (Md) rallies past Boston U 91-86 in OT
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Cam Gregory scored 18 points, Denzel Brito drilled a go-ahead 3-pointer with 57 seconds left in overtime, and Loyola of Maryland defeated Boston University 91-86 on Sunday. The Greyhounds (7-10, 3-3 Patriot League) had six players in double figures, including all starters. Andre Walker finished with 17 points, Eric Laster had 15 and Franz Rassman 14. Cheddi Mosely had 23 points to lead BU (7-10, 3-3), which shot 48.1 percent but went 22 of 41 on free throws. Loyola rallied from a seven-point deficit in regulation, as Brito made a 3 with less than a second left. A flagrant foul on BU led to two free throws from Rassman to tie it. A foul on the inbounds pass gave BU's Eric Fanning two free throws, which he missed. After two free throws from Mosely in overtime, Brito hit his go-ahead 3-pointer and Walker sealed it with four late free throws.
